  "body": "## ðŸŽ‰ Description\r\n\r\nI have the problem with the listener in ERC-721 contract - it failed < Geth 1.8.x. I created a test contract to isolate the problem. The contract below works correctly on Geth 1.8.x. \r\n\r\n- [X] ðŸ› This is a bug report.\r\n\r\n## ðŸ’» Environment\r\n\r\n- OpenZeppelin 1.12.0\r\n- Geth 1.7.2 or Quorum\r\n- Truffle v4.1.13\r\n\r\n## ðŸ”¢ Code To Reproduce Issue [ Good To Have ]\r\n\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.24;\r\n\r\nimport \"openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/token/ERC721/ERC721Token.sol\";\r\n\r\n\r\ncontract ERC721test is ERC721Token(\"TEST\", \"T\") {\r\n\r\n    event A(uint256 i);\r\n\r\n    uint256 private index;\r\n\r\n    function make(address _to, uint256 _index) public {\r\n        safeTransferFrom(msg.sender, _to, _index);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function c(address _to) public {\r\n        ERC721Receiver receiver = ERC721Receiver(_to);\r\n\r\n        receiver\r\n            .onERC721Received\r\n        (\r\n            _to,\r\n            _to,\r\n            1,\r\n            toBytesNickJohnson(1)\r\n        );\r\n\r\n        emit A(1);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function mint() public {\r\n        _mint(msg.sender, index++);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function toBytesNickJohnson(uint256 x) internal pure returns (bytes b) {\r\n        b = new bytes(32);\r\n        assembly { mstore(add(b, 32), x) }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\npragma solidity ^0.4.24;\r\n\r\nimport \"openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/token/ERC721/ERC721Receiver.sol\";\r\n\r\n\r\ncontract Listener is ERC721Receiver {\r\n\r\n    event Received(uint256 id);\r\n\r\n\r\n    function onERC721Received(\r\n        address _operator,\r\n        address _from,\r\n        uint256 _tokenId,\r\n        bytes _data\r\n    )\r\n    public\r\n    returns(bytes4) {\r\n\r\n        emit Received(_tokenId);\r\n\r\n        return ERC721_RECEIVED;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n ",
